SIMPLE: sextillion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sextillion
<hw>Sex*til"lion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Formed (in
imitation of <ets>million</ets>) fr. L. <ets>sextus</ets> sixth,
<ets>sex</ets> six: cf. F. <ets>sextilion</ets>.]</ety> <def>According
to the method of numeration (which is followed also in the United
States), the number expressed by a unit with twenty-one ciphers annexed.
According to the English method, a million raised to the sixth power, or
the number expressed by a unit with thirty-six ciphers annexed. See
<er>Numeration</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sexto</ent>⟦br⟧
